###################################################################################################################################################
The Nautilus application development team has shared that they are planning to deploy one newly developed application on Nautilus infra in Stratos DC. 
The application uses PostgreSQL database, so as a pre-requisite we need to set up PostgreSQL database server as per requirements shared below:


PostgreSQL database server is already installed on the Nautilus database server.


a. Create a database user kodekloud_joy and set its password to LQfKeWWxWD.


b. Create a database kodekloud_db7 and grant full permissions to user kodekloud_joy on this database.


Note: Please do not try to restart PostgreSQL server service.
###################################################################################################################################################


Since PostgreSQL is already installed and running on the Nautilus database server, we only need to create the user and database, and assign privileges.
(Do not restart the PostgreSQL service.)

Login to the Nautilus DB Server and switch to the postgres user:

sudo -i -u postgres


Open the PostgreSQL shell:

psql


Now run the following SQL commands:

a) Create the database user
CREATE USER kodekloud_joy WITH PASSWORD 'LQfKeWWxWD';

b) Create the database
CREATE DATABASE kodekloud_db7;

c) Grant full permissions on the database to the user
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE kodekloud_db7 TO kodekloud_joy;


Exit PostgreSQL:

\q


Exit from postgres user:

exit

Verification (Optional)
psql -U kodekloud_joy -d kodekloud_db7 -h localhost


If it connects successfully, the setup is correct.

✔ User kodekloud_joy created
✔ Database kodekloud_db7 created
✔ Full access granted
✔ PostgreSQL service untouched





